cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the use of deep learning methods, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNN), and their performance on imbalanced data sets with a small number of training samples. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). However, given the focus on deep learning methods and their performance on imbalanced data sets, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories.
